    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<h1 id="Things-about-Archlinux"><a href="#Things-about-Archlinux" class="headerlink" title="Things about Archlinux"></a>Things about Archlinux</h1><h2 id="Installation"><a href="#Installation" class="headerlink" title="Installation:"></a>Installation:</h2><ul><li>bilibili video,  <a href="https://www.bilibili.com/video/BV1qf4y1D7Da">https://www.bilibili.com/video/BV1qf4y1D7Da</a>,<br>  mostly official document,<br>  remember to add arachlinuxcn as pacman source, fcitx5 as Chinese method</li></ul><h2 id="KDE-settings"><a href="#KDE-settings" class="headerlink" title="KDE settings:"></a>KDE settings:</h2><ul><li><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=exQh0_JKBJQ">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=exQh0_JKBJQ</a>, <strong>good firefox theme</strong></li></ul><h2 id="Install-QQ-or-Wechat"><a href="#Install-QQ-or-Wechat" class="headerlink" title="Install QQ or Wechat:"></a>Install QQ or Wechat:</h2><pre><code>sudo pacman -S base-devel #things for installing packagesyay -S com.qq.weixin.deepin # deepin, yyds</code></pre><p>still can’t figure out how to use qq or tim on KDE, but wechat is ok</p>]]></content>
    
    
